a299b2d\"\n      ],\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:-5163901258\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"main_bot\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/8e0cb2bc-8245-4c89-bc2c-e3cca2257d0f.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Night silence rule: 23:00-07:00 UTC+7 = 16:00-00:00 UTC. Current time is 00:51 UTC (00:51 + 7 = 07:51 UTC+7). That's past the morning window. Actually 00:51 UTC = 07:51 UTC+7 which is past the 07:00 cutoff. So normal reply.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"HEARTBEAT_OK\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 190,\n            \"output\": 93,\n            \"totalTokens\": 101018,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 100735,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776214455278,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e14b9576f6b1aefdec9ea4e9e736a\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"c356d232\",\n            \"seq\": 1189\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 01:06 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• COMPLETED: cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV monitor) — finished normally, next run due ~01:08 UTC ✅\\n• COMPLETED: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — status report delivered to Lead ✅\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n• Active sessions: 3 (cron:6f3323ef ✅ telegram:direct ✅ this group ✅)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: none\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1776215411744,\n          \"provenance\": {\n            \"kind\": \"inter_session\",\n            \"sourceSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n            \"sourceChannel\": \"telegram\",\n            \"sourceTool\": \"sessions_send\"\n          },\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"304bcd4c\",\n            \"seq\": 1190\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Skip.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"\\nHEARTBEAT_OK\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 187,\n            \"output\": 11,\n            \"totalTokens\": 101166,\n            \"cacheRead\": 7778,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 93190,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776215411903,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e187577dd7ca909bc6a98eea9f9d3\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"26df346c\",\n            \"seq\": 1191\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"heartbeat\"\n      },\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776215194808,\n      \"sessionId\": \"272b4d51-b59f-4655-acbf-c33f81e2bda6\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 57294,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776199558073,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/272b4d51-b59f-4655-acbf-c33f81e2bda6.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The sessions_send timed out again. The group session seems to not respond. Let me try using sessions_history to check the current state, and if needed, try the other method.\\n\\nActually, the problem is that sessions_send waits for the target session to reply, but the group session is in a \\\"done\\\" state (it ends and receives heartbeats). The message was likely delivered though.\\n\\nLet me check if the message was delivered by looking at the session history.\\n\\nActually, I notice the group session status was \\\"running\\\" when it was \\\"done\\\" in the current check. But its last message was HEARTBEAT_OK at 00:51 UTC, and its status shows \\\"running\\\" with `endedAt: 1776163783190`. \\n\\nSo the session ended around 16:49 UTC on April 14th, which means it's definitely done and can't process the message I just sent. The timeout on sessions_send makes sense now—the target session isn't active to receive or respond to anything.\\n\\nLooking back at the heartbeat data, the group session was marked as \\\"running\\\" at the last check at 01:03 UTC, but its endedAt timestamp shows it actually finished at 16:49 UTC. That inconsistency is odd—the session should've been marked as done in the heartbeat state. Either way, since it's ended, it can't process new messages. But I'm wondering if the delivery confirmation was about something else entirely, or if the message was queued for a future session. I should probably stop trying to send messages to this ended session and just report back that the task is complete. the heartbeat state is what matters for determining if I should send a report. Looking at the current state, the group session is still running at 01:06 UTC, so the message would likely be delivered if I try again, though it might just return HEARTBEAT_OK instead of processing the content. Since the delivery shows timeout but the group session is marked as running, I should attempt to send the report one more time, but I need to be careful not to spam the channel. Let me just report what I've accomplished so far: updating the heartbeat state and attempting to send the report to the group session, even though it timed out.\\n\\nActually, I'm overthinking this. The task just says to return a summary as plain text that gets delivered automatically. Since I've already updated the heartbeat state and tried sending the report to the group session, I should just report that the 5p update was sent to group -5163901258, noting the delivery timeout but that the message was likely queued. But wait—the task specifically says \\\"compose a concise change report to group -5163901258\\\" and to only send when something changed. So the report should go to that Telegram group, not just back to this cron session.\\n\\nLet me try using sessions_yield instead to see if that works better for the reporting task.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"The group session responded with timeout. Let me try once more with a shorter timeout to confirm delivery:\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_18fryiul7oci_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_send\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258\",\n                \"message\": \"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 01:06 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• COMPLETED: cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV monitor) — finished normally, next run ~01:08 UTC ✅\\n• COMPLETED: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — status delivered to Lead ✅\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n• Active sessions: 3 (DTLX 5p ✅ Lead direct ✅ group ✅)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: none\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\",\n                \"timeoutSeconds\": 15\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 177,\n            \"output\": 818,\n            \"totalTokens\": 57222,\n            \"cacheRead\": 55034,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 1193,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776215333737,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e182780785e5394fbf5fda6ea1585\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"52c0c16a\",\n            \"seq\": 13\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The group session keeps timing out. This is a persistent issue. The group session likely is in a state where it can't receive messages. The \\\"delivery confirmed\\\" in earlier cron runs may have been a false positive (the message was queued but never delivered).\\n\\nThe issue is that sessions_send waits for the target session to reply with an assistant message, but the group session doesn't produce an assistant response - it just echoes HEARTBEAT_OK. So it always times out.\\n\\nI should report this as the task output. The report was composed and attempted, but the group session delivery keeps timing out. This is a known issue that the SOUL.md/TOOLS.md protocols mention.\\n \\nThe task wants the report delivered automatically, but if Telegram delivery keeps failing, I need to surface this blocker instead of silently timing out again. I'll document that the 5p update was composed and attempted to the group session, but delivery keeps failing. since it's in a \\\"running\\\" state in sessions_list but times out on every attempt, this seems like a bug in how the group session reports its state.\\n\\nGiven the persistent timeout issue, I should just report the facts: the heartbeat state has been updated, the 5p update was composed and attempted to group -5163901258, but delivery is timing out repeatedly. This could indicate the group session is stale and needs to be restarted, or there's a deeper issue with how messages are being routed. I'll output the report summary with the delivery failure noted, keeping it minimal since the instructions emphasize conciseness.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"The group session persistently times out on `sessions_send`. This is a known pattern — the session shows \\\"running\\\" but never replies to inter-session messages, causing delivery timeouts. The report was composed and the heartbeat state updated, but delivery to group -5163901258 could not be confirmed.\\n\\n**Summary for auto-delivery:**\\n\\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 01:06 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• COMPLETED: cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV monitor) — finished normally, next run ~01:08 UTC ✅\\n• COMPLETED: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — status delivered to Lead ✅\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n• Active sessions: 3 (DTLX 5p ✅ Lead direct ✅ group ✅)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: none\\n\\n⚠️ Telegram delivery to group -5163901